column3: Summary
column6: Examples of tools or services from AWS, Azure and GCP

column3: A gateway pattern that offloads common tasks, such as routing, authentication, and security, from backend services.
column6: Amazon API Gateway, Azure Application Gateway, Google Cloud Endpoints

column3: A pattern that isolates a new system from changes to an existing system.
column6: AWS Glue, Azure Data Factory, Google Cloud Data Fusion

column3: A pattern that allows backend services to respond to requests asynchronously.
column6: Amazon SQS, Azure Service Bus, Google Cloud Pub/Sub

column3: A pattern that provides separate backend services for different types of clients, such as web and mobile clients.
column6: AWS Lambda, Azure Functions, Google Cloud Functions

column3: A pattern that isolates different parts of a system to prevent cascading failures.
column6: Amazon EC2 Availability Zones, Azure Availability Zones, Google Cloud Regions

column3: A pattern that caches frequently accessed data to improve performance.
column6: Amazon ElastiCache, Azure Redis Cache, Google Cloud Memorystore

column3: A pattern that coordinates the execution of tasks across multiple distributed services.
column6: Amazon Step Functions, Azure Logic Apps, Google Cloud Workflows

column3: A pattern that prevents cascading failures by automatically failing requests to a service that is unavailable or unresponsive.
column6: Netflix Hystrix, Azure Resilience Toolkit, Google Cloud Resilience

column3: A pattern that splits a large message into smaller parts to improve scalability.
column6: Amazon S3, Azure Blob Storage, Google Cloud Storage

column3: A pattern that separates the read and write operations of a data store to improve performance and scalability.
column6: Amazon DynamoDB, Azure Cosmos DB, Google Cloud Bigtable

column3: A pattern that allows multiple consumers to process messages from a queue in parallel.
column6: Amazon Kinesis, Azure Event Hubs, Google Cloud Pub/Sub

column3: A pattern that combines multiple workloads onto a single server to improve efficiency.
column6: AWS Reserved Instances, Azure Reserved VMs, Google Cloud Committed Use discounts

column3: A pattern that divides a large database into smaller, more manageable databases.
column6: Amazon Aurora, Azure SQL Database, Google Cloud Spanner

column3: A pattern that stores changes to a system as a sequence of events.
column6: Amazon Kinesis Data Streams, Azure Event Hubs, Google Cloud Pub/Sub

column3: A pattern that stores the configuration of a system in a central location.
column6: AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store, Azure Key Vault, Google Cloud Secret Manager

column3: A pattern that allows users to authenticate to a service using their credentials from another service.
column6: AWS Single Sign-On, Azure Active Directory, Google Cloud Identity and Access Management (IAM)

column3: A pattern that controls access to a service by authenticating and authorizing users.
column6: AWS Cognito, Azure Active Directory, Google Cloud IAM

column3: A pattern that monitors the health of a service and alerts operators when problems are detected.
column6: AWS CloudWatch, Azure Monitor, Google Cloud Monitoring

column3: A pattern that uses an index table to improve the performance of queries.
column6: Amazon DynamoDB Global Secondary Indexes, Azure Cosmos DB Partitions and Indexes, Google Cloud Bigtable

column3: A pattern that elects a single node to be the leader of a cluster.
column6: ZooKeeper, Raft, Consul

column3: A pattern that creates a materialized view of a data store to improve the performance of queries.
column6: Amazon Redshift Spectrum, Azure Synapse Analytics, Google Cloud Dataproc

column3: A pattern that decomposes a task into a sequence of smaller, simpler tasks.
column6: Apache Spark, Apache Beam, Google Cloud Dataflow

column3: A pattern that prioritizes messages in a queue to ensure that the most important messages are processed first.
column6: Amazon Simple Queue Service (SQS), Azure Service Bus, Google Cloud Pub/Sub

column3: A pattern that uses a queue to distribute traffic across multiple backend services.
column6: Amazon SQS, Azure Service Bus, Google Cloud Pub/Sub

column3: A pattern that automatically retries requests that fail due to transient errors.
column6: AWS Polly, Azure Speech Service, Google Cloud Text-to-Speech
